\par\par \uc2 NATIONAL NEWS\par \b \uc2 ANTICIPATING POTENTIAL OF COVID-19 BECOMING ENDEMIC: GOVT\b0\par\par\uc2 338 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 August 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - The Indonesian Government is anticipating the likelihood of the COVID-19 pandemic becoming endemic based on scientific research, Head of \b \highlight22\uc2 Fiscal Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  at the Finance MinistryFebrio Kacaribu has said.\par \par \uc2 "Of course, we will continue to anticipate every latest development. (The question is) How should we prepare ourselves as an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  nation," he said during an online discussion here on Wednesday.\par \par \uc2 Kacaribu was referring to a Nature Magazine survey of 119 immunologists, infectious-disease researchers, and virologists in 23 countries.\par \par \uc2 "When asked about how likely do you think that SARS-CoV-2 will become an endemic virus, 89 percent of them answered that it is very likely to become endemic," Kacaribu highlighted.\par \par \uc2 The government must hence remain focused on protecting the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 "s safety in confronting the risk and the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  of COVID-19, he added.\par \par \uc2 The steps that have been implemented to prepare for living with the pandemic involve making the 5Ms -- masking, hand washing, social distancing, crowd avoidance, mobility reduction -- a culture, and intensifying the implementation of the 3Ts -- testing, tracing, treatment, he informed.\par \par \uc2 Creating a reliable and prepared health system is also a step that has been implemented, he added.\par \par \uc2 Kacaribu noted that the government will also expedite the vaccination program since this is the main strategy for ensuring sustainable recovery.\par \par \uc2 Indonesia is experiencing an outstanding development in vaccination acceleration, he said.\par \par \uc2 Vaccinations have crossed one million on average per day in Indonesia to the point where the country has been ranked ninth in vaccination realization in the world, he added.\par \par \uc2 "This is something that we continue to push since we cannot be satisfied with 1.15 million per day as of August 17 (2021)," he remarked.\par \par \uc2 The government is targeting to vaccinate around 70 percent of Indonesia"s total population, or 208 million people, by the end of the year so that citizens confidence in carrying out activities can improve.\par \par \uc2 (T.KR-FLI/A/R013/R013) 18-08-2021 19:29:03\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020210818eh8i001e1\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
