\par\par \b \uc2 BI-government burden sharing needs to be limited\b0\par\par\uc2 696 \uc2 words\par \uc2 30 August 2021\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2021 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Haryo Kuncoro, Jakarta\par \par \uc2 The government and \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) \uc2 agreed again last week to share the financing burdens of health care and social assistance for the 2021-2022 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year. Under the agreement BI will buy from the primary market government bonds (SBN) amounting to Rp 215 trillion (US$15.03 billion) in 2021 and Rp 224 trillion in 2022. BI will bear the interest on Rp 90 trillion of the total amount while the government will pay the interest on the remaining Rp 349 trillion at the BI seven-day reverse repo rate, which is much lower than the market rate.\par \par \uc2 In many other countries, central banks also contributed to the financing of \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  deficits that have risen sharply during the COVID-19 pandemic. The United States, for example, bought government bonds to fund \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Up to this point, the side effects of the burden sharing scheme seem to be within the control of BI and the government. However, BI's direct support in the burden sharing scheme still needs extra caution. The large volume of SBN absorption by BI will disrupt the market equilibrium. The burden sharing will decrease SBN issuance through regular auctions from Rp 632 trillion to around Rp 417 trillion in the second half of this year, thereby causing tight market competition.\par \par \uc2 The purchase of SBN by BI in the primary market will be immediately monetized. This is because the rupiah SBN is a new issuance and has a long tenor (five to eight years), and is tradable in the market. As a result, bond market instability is a price that must be addressed in the burden sharing. The type of SBN purchased by BI can indeed be used as an instrument for monetary operations. However, the commitment to buying SBN when the monetary situation does not require it will have an impact on the effectiveness of the monetary instrument itself.\par \par \uc2 The accumulated tension of financial market instability will increase when the taper tantrum (money tightening)\b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is imposed by the US \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The taper tantrum, estimated to start later this year, will increase the US benchmark interest rate and this would trigger capital outflows from emerging economies such as Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 The third volume of the burden sharing scheme is projected to shrink BI's equity by 8.9 percent in the current year and is likely to shrink again by 4 or 5 percent for the next year.\par \par \uc2 Such conditions would prompt foreign investors to unload their rupiah bonds and BI would again have to buy SBN in the secondary market. Certainly, the rupiah sterilization \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  must also be pursued through intervention in the spot market. The foreign exchange market intervention and the purchase of SBN in the midst of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  are very expensive. The BI's foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  and equity could be eroded.\par \par \uc2 The above concern seems to be reasonable. The burden sharing scheme series I and II in 2020 have reduced 8.64 percent of BI's capital ratio. The third volume of the burden sharing scheme is projected to shrink BI's equity by 8.9 percent in the current year and is likely to shrink again by 4 or 5 percent for the next year.\par \par \uc2 Under the problematic configuration above, the burden sharing scheme needs to be guarded by definitive clauses regarding the limit on how much BI must bear the burden and how long it will end. The government also should re-emphasize that burden sharing is a one off \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to deal with the C0VID-19 pandemic.\par \par \uc2 The ceiling in the amount and the fixed period of the burden sharing will enable BI to balance short and long-term interest and to cope with internal and external challenges. After all, stabilization is a key prerequisite for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. Eventually, if the stability can be maintained and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery can be strengthened, the credibility and independence of BI's monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will be sustained.\par \par \uc2 _________________\par \par \uc2 A professor of economics at the School of Economics, Jakarta State University, and research director at the Socio-\b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  & Educational Business Institute (SEEBI) Jakarta. The views expressed are his own.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020210829eh8u0000c\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
