\par\par \uc2 NATIONAL NEWS\par \b \uc2 COOPERATION BETWEEN COUNTRIES ESSENTIAL TO TACKLE PANDEMIC: MINISTER\b0\par\par\uc2 406 \uc2 words\par \uc2 17 September 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - Solid cooperation between countries is essential for battling the coronavirus pandemic, Minister of Communication and Informatics Johnny G. Plate has said.\par \par \uc2 "The COVID-19 pandemic situation is an \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  and difficult situation for everyone in the world. No single country can fight this pandemic alone, so strong cooperation is needed, including between countries," the minister remarked while receiving Indian Ambassador to Indonesia, Shri Manoj Kumar Bharti, at his official residence here on Thursday.\par \par \uc2 The government appreciates any aid received from abroad as a tangible form of solidarity, he said adding, Indonesia has close relations with several countries.\par \par \uc2 During the meeting, the minister highlighted the two focus areas of the government for dealing with the pandemic \u8212\'20\'14 the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and health sectors.\par \par \uc2 In the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  sector, the Proud of Made-in IndonesiaProducts Movement is one of the steps that have been taken to accelerate national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery, he said.\par \par \uc2 "We continue to encourage the strengthening and benefits of the digital \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  because currently, the backbone of the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is MSMEs and Ultra Micro (Enterprises) that contribute 61.07 percent to Indonesia"s GDP," he added.\par \par \uc2 The government has also permitted restaurants and shopping centers to reopen while following the rules for implementing restrictions on \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities, Plate said.\par \par \uc2 The government continues to strive to implement comprehensive policies to support national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery, one of which is by making innovations in the technology sector and preparing digital talents to support the improvement of the digital \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he added.\par \par \uc2 To secure \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  health, he said, the government is following a \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of implementing \b \highlight22\uc2 Public\b0 \highlight\uc2  Activity Restrictions (PPKM) by taking into account the situation and conditions in each region.\par \par \uc2 "This (PPKM) aims to reduce the trend of spikes in new cases of the COVID-19 delta variant," the minister explained.\par \par \uc2 Community compliance and discipline are the primary keys to reduce the level of accurate PPKM assessments, Plate said. According to data provided on the website covid19.go.id page, Indonesia"s positivity rate stood below 5 percent as of September 14, 2021.\par \par \uc2 "For this achievement, the government appreciates the efforts and hard work of all parties. However, I still urge all elements of the nation to remain disciplined, not be careless and complacent in the euphoria of decreasing positive cases of COVID-19," Plate said.\par \par \uc2 (T.KR-RAP/A/S022/S022) 17-09-2021 18:30:47\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020210917eh9h000xd\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Ups and Downs over Olefin Refinery\b0\par\par\uc2 2,289 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 September 2021\par \uc2 Tempo Magazine\par \uc2 TEMGEN\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk. \par \par \uc2 THE long awaited letter by tender participants for the construction project design of \uc2 Trans-Pacific Petrochemical Indotama\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s (TPPI) olefin refinery in Tuban, East Java, was finally issued by Kilang \uc2 Pertamina\uc2  Internasional (KPI) on Monday, 6 September. The \uc2 Pertamina\uc2  subsidiary, which oversees TPPI, appointed two bidders as winners of the tender.\par \par \uc2 The bid winners are the joint operation \uc2 Hyundai Engineering Co Ltd\uc2 -Rekayasa Industri-Enviromate Technology International-Saipem SpA and the Technip Italy SpA-Tripatra Engineers and Constructors-Technip Indonesia-Samsung Engineering Co Ltd consortium. \u8220\'20\'1CDuration: 270 calendar days from the kick-off meeting,\u8221\'20\'1D said the letter, signed by KPI\u8217\'20\'19s Vice President for Project, Contract, and Services Procurement Muchamad Lutfi as the head of the tender team.\par \par \uc2 The tender value of this design package was not a lot. Referring to KPI\u8217\'20\'19s letter, the Hyundai joint operation and the \uc2 Technip\uc2  consortium offered similar prices, around Rp789.5 billion excluding the value-added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 . With an additional \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  fund of Rp22 billion for each participant, the contract\u8217\'20\'19s total value is estimated at just Rp1.57 trillion.\par \par \uc2 But winning the bid is vital. Both winners would compete again for the front-end engineering design (FEED). Over the next nine months, they would be compiling a more accurate estimate on engineering, procurement, and construction (EPC) costs. The party that makes the lowest bid would be chosen to carry out the factory construction.\par \par \uc2 Workers at the \uc2 Trans Pacific Petrochemical Indotama\uc2  (TPPI) Oil Refinery in Tuban, East Java, November 2015. Antara/Widodo S. Jusuf\par \par \uc2 The TPPI olefin megaproject is designed as an integrated refinery complex. The complex will consist of four factories, an olefin cracker plant with a capacity of 1,000 kilotons per year, high-density polyethylene or linear low-density polyethylene factory (700 kilotons per year), a low-density polyethylene factory (300 kilotons per year), and polypropylene\u8212\'20\'14or high-impact polypropylene\u8212\'20\'14factory (600 kilotons per year). The total investment value is estimated at Rp50 trillion and more.\par \par \uc2 At TPPI\u8217\'20\'19s operating area in Remen village, Tuban, there is actually already an aromatic refinery built. Back then, the infrastructure was designed to be a petrochemical refinery that produces aromatics and olefins. The condensate (naphtha) derivative product is a raw material for the synthetic fiber and textile industry, as well as the plastic industry for packaging, building, and automotive needs.\par \par \uc2 But the 1998 monetary crisis crushed that idea. The plan to build the olefin refinery was canceled over funding issues. And so, the TTPI\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  value as an aromatic refinery only becomes less than not optimal. The sales prices of the product it has been producing\u8212\'20\'14light naphtha\u8212\'20\'14are lower than the price of the raw material. Ideally, light naphtha is used as a raw material for making olefins.\par \par \uc2 At the end of 2019, President Joko Widodo launched the continuation of the TPPI for the olefin refinery project. At the time, the government officially took over the management of TPPI through \uc2 Pertamina\uc2 , after converting the bad debt of the old owner, Honggo Wendratno. Jokowi gave an instruction: the refinery construction project must be completed in three years.\par \par \uc2 However, the project was not progressing as loud as the president\u8217\'20\'19s instruction. Since \uc2 Pertamina\uc2  opened the prequalification tender registration at the beginning of last year, a series of issues started surfacing. In fact, the results of the design package auction, which had stalled for months, also have problems now.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22\u8226\'20\'22\u8226\'20\'22\par \par \uc2 OPENED at the end of February 2020, the tender for the TPPI\u8217\'20\'19s olefin refinery project was planned using the design build competition concept. The scheme covers four jobs at the same time: technology selection, basic engineering design, FEED, and EPC. In the initial announcement, \uc2 Pertamina\uc2  invited consortiums that have the required knowledge, expertise, technical qualifications, experience, and financial capabilities in similar projects.\par \par \uc2 Of the six that registered, four participants passed the pre-qualification stage. In addition to the joint operation of Hyundai and the \uc2 Technip\uc2  consortium, the other two participants were GS Engineering & Construction Corp-Adhi Karya-Tecnimont SpA consortium, and the \uc2 Daelim Industrial Co Ltd\uc2 -Wijaya Karya-McDermott Indonesia consortium. Later, GS Engineering and Daelim consortium were eliminated from the final round of tenders in September 2020.\par \par \uc2 Trans Pacific Petrochemical Indotama\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s (TPPI) refinery in Tuban, East Java, December 2019. Antara/Moch Asim\par \par \uc2 Problems began surfacing towards the end of 2020. \uc2 Pertamina\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s Board of Commissioners questioned a number of things. According to two Pertamina Group officials who participated in the tender process, the Board of Commissioners judged that \uc2 Pertamina\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s management was unable to prepare the auction properly. The tender implementer, for example, submits the financing plan and technology selection to the bidders.\par \par \uc2 Normally, project owners would first prepare various project plans, to ensure that the refinery built would meet the company\u8217\'20\'19s goals. The classification of technology to use, for example, is determined by the type of olefin products they want. That way, the project planning also requires mapping out market projections and future marketing strategies.\par \par \uc2 The problem was, according to the two Tempo sources, there were suspicions that Refinery \uc2 Pertamina\uc2  Internasional\u8212\'20\'14as the executor of the tender\u8212\'20\'14did not involve TPPI management, who would be the operator of operations and marketing of refinery products. This information angered \uc2 Pertamina\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s President Commissioner, Basuki Tjahaja Purnama. Basuki was concerned that TPPI would not be able to provide optimal revenue for the company if the tender was not designed optimally. He asked the board of directors to review the implementation of the tender, including the possibility of holding a re-auction.\par \par \uc2 In a letter titled The Board of Commissioners\u8217\'20\'19 Directions regarding the TPPI Olefin Project dated January 19, the Pertamina Board of Commissioners reprimanded the directors of the Pertamina International Refinery and asked them to involve \uc2 Tuban Petrochemical Industries\uc2 \u8212\'20\'14the parent of TPPI\u8212\'20\'14in the project planning and implementation. The planning in question, as the letter stated, covers aspects of business, technical, finance, marketing, and legal. The directive refers to the meeting of the Audit Committee and Investment Committee of the Board of Commissioners held with the Directorate of Strategy, Portfolio and Business Development of Refinery Pertamina Internasional and Tuban Petrochemical on January 7.\par \par \uc2 Basuki, also known as Ahok, was not willing to provide an explanation regarding this matter. \u8220\'20\'1CJust ask the directors,\u8221\'20\'1D said the former Jakarta governor.\par \par \uc2 The tensions between \uc2 Pertamina\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s directors and the Board of Commissioners is the reason why the tender process was stalled for months. The Board of Commissioners also questioned why \uc2 Hyundai Engineering\uc2 , which previously won the auction for the Balikpapan Refinery Development Master Plan (RDMP) project, leads the consortium consisting of Rekayasa Industri a.k.a. Rekind and Pembangunan Perumahan.\par \par \uc2 Initially, this consortium was led by \uc2 SK Engineering & Construction Co Ltd\uc2 , a well-known contractor from South Korea. Later, SK resigned, and was replaced by \uc2 Hyundai Engineering\uc2  as the consortium leader.\par \par \uc2 The Board of Commissioners smelled something fishy about the RDMP project, which has a contract value of Rp57.8 trillion. In addition to swelling costs, the work realization was considered sub-par. The project is certainly delayed from the original plan. Later, the Finance and Development Supervisory Agency (BPKP) was asked to audit this project.\par \par \uc2 Refinery Pertamina International Corporate Secretary Ifki Sukarya admitted that the Balikpapan RDMP project faced some obstacles. He blamed the Covid-19 pandemic, which prompted a number of major refinery manufacturing countries to impose lockdowns. As a result, he said, the provision of the main equipment was delayed. The same problem occurred in labor mobilization. \u8220\'20\'1CThere were also unforeseen materials during the land clearing process of project construction,\u8221\'20\'1D said Ifki on Friday, September 17. \u8220\'20\'1CDespite these obstacles, the project by the Hyundai-Rekind joint operation is performing quite well.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22\u8226\'20\'22\u8226\'20\'22\par \par \uc2 IN the Board of Commissioners\u8217\'20\'19 Direction letter, it was revealed that \uc2 Pertamina\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s directors proposed for the TPPI olefin project to be continued using a design build competition (DBC) strategy. For that, a contract awarding DBC stage 1 is needed by the end of January, in order to achieve the target to operate the factory by the end of 2024. At the time, the management also stated that they have bagged the names of the two best participants, the Hyundai joint operation and the \uc2 Technip\uc2  consortium.\par \par \uc2 The two bid winners that made the tender cut offer different technologies in each type of plant. For the olefin refinery, for example, Hyundai offers technology by \uc2 Kellogg Brown & Root\uc2  (KBR)\u8212\'20\'14which was once in the same group with Halliburton, United States. Meanwhile, \uc2 Technip\uc2  proposed the \uc2 Technip\uc2  technology from France.\par \par \uc2 According to an official that follows the process, TPPI neither wanted KBR nor \uc2 Technip\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s technology for the olefin factory. The basis for their refusal refers to the trend of the olefin refinery technology used in the world. A Tempo source explained that 55 percent of the world\u8217\'20\'19s olefin factory built over the last decade has used the Lummus technology. Twenty-five percent used \uc2 Technip\uc2  technology, and the rest used other technologies\u8212\'20\'14including KBR. \u8220\'20\'1CTuban Petro and TPPI wanted proven technology, and the most commonly used is Lummus,\u8221\'20\'1D the source said.\par \par \uc2 Differences also occur in the polypropylene plant design. Hyundai brought in the Grace technology from the United States, while \uc2 Technip\uc2  brought Lummus Novolen Technology Polypropylene. During the tender, the chosen technology license was Grace. However, the letter revealed that the TPPI needed the \uc2 LyondellBasell\uc2  technology from the Netherlands. This type of technology has been included in the list of licenses that would be used. However, \uc2 LyondellBasell\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s internal rules only allowed the signing of license agreements with the project owner, in this case, \uc2 Pertamina\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 President Jokowi together with Pertamina President Commissioner Basuki Tjahaja Purnama inspecting the TPPI\u8217\'20\'19s refinery in Tuban, East Java, last December. BPMI\par \par \uc2 Pertamina\uc2  reasoned, as stated in the Board of Commissioners letter, that the directors select which technology to use in the TPPI olefin project by making a list of licensors, which they would give to bidders. Participants would then negotiate with the license owners. In the design build competition scheme, all project obligations are centered on the contractor. This means that the licensor signs a licensing agreement and engineering agreement with the contractor, not the project owner.\par \par \uc2 The tender scheme proposed by \uc2 Pertamina\uc2  was seen as confusing by a number of oil and gas as well as petrochemicals practitioners. Ari Soemarno, a former chief executive officer (CEO) of \uc2 Pertamina\uc2 , said that the sequence of stages of development of the TPPI olefin project was wrong. Ideally, he said, the project owner determines the desired technology first. \u8220\'20\'1CWe have to know which technology is the most suitable. Even if we need to find a consultant for it. It\u8217\'20\'19s not the contractor who decides, who is the owner of this project?\u8221\'20\'1D said Ari. He likened the design build competition\u8217\'20\'19s structure and concept to a lazy person who leaves everything for the contractors to handle, and the project owner only acts as a supervisor.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22\u8226\'20\'22\u8226\'20\'22\par \par \uc2 PROBLEMS and confusions over the \uc2 Trans-Pacific Petrochemical Indotama\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s olefin project were not only caused by the refusal from \uc2 Pertamina\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s Board of Commissioners. The GS Engineering & Construction Corp-Adhi Karma and \uc2 Tecnimont SpA\uc2  consortium also filed a rebuttal over the determination of the winner of the auction to Pertamina CEO Nicke Widyawati.\par \par \uc2 In the letter dated May 24, the GS Engineering consortium mentions a number of irregularities in the auction process. They questioned the selection of \uc2 Hyundai Engineering Co Ltd\uc2 , which they saw as having no experience in completing the engineering, procurement and construction of an olefin refinery. The consortium claimed that \uc2 Hyundai Engineering\uc2  never built the olefin refinery construction to completion. The portfolio attached to Hyundai was for a gas chemical complex project in Turkmenistan. According to GS Engineering\u8217\'20\'19s disclaimer, it was \uc2 Toyo Engineering\uc2  that worked on the project\u8217\'20\'19s EPC and FEED, as stated in the official Toyo website.\par \par \uc2 Another oddity, according to the GS consortium, is the fact that Hyundai Engineering and Construction Co Ltd.\u8212\'20\'14the parent of \uc2 Hyundai Engineering Co\uc2 .\u8212\'20\'14is currently implicated in a bribery case being handled by the Corruption Eradication Commission \uc2 Corruption Eradication Commission (KPK)\uc2 . Presidential Decree No. 80/2003 and Presidential \b \highlight22\uc2 Regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  No. 16/2018 stated that companies involved in corruption are not allowed to participate in national strategic project tenders.\par \par \uc2 Kilang Pertamina Internasional Corporate Secretary Ifki Sukarya ensured that \uc2 Pertamina\uc2  had evaluated the documents from the bidders in accordance with the terms and conditions of the prequalification documents. \u8220\'20\'1C(Based on) the results of document evaluation and clarification to project owner Kiyanly Turkmengas, (the appointment of) Hyundai as a leader in the consortium has met the requirements,\u8221\'20\'1D he said on Saturday, September 18.\par \par \uc2 Regarding the case at the KPK, Ifki said \uc2 Pertamina\uc2  believes \uc2 Hyundai Engineering & Construction Co Ltd\uc2  and \uc2 Hyundai Engineering Co Ltd\uc2  are two different companies. \uc2 Pertamina\uc2 , he said, received confirmation from the South Korean embassy. Ifki also asserted that the company has tasked its internal audit unit and a team from the Attorney General\u8217\'20\'19s Office to oversee this tender process.\par \par \uc2 With these beliefs, Refinery \uc2 Pertamina\uc2  Internasional announced the results of the tender early last September, even though the commotion had not subsided. Basuki Tjahaja Purnama claimed he did not know about the tender announcement. \u8220\'20\'1CThey do not need to report to the Board of Commissioners,\u8221\'20\'1D he said.\par \par \uc2 Even Basuki could not confirm which technology would be used in the TPPI olefin project, the one offered by the bidders or the one that would accommodate TPPI\u8217\'20\'19s needs. The decision about this would be made clear after the next 270 days, as written in the letter from the head of the tender team, Muchamad Lutfi.\par \par \uc2 RETNO SULISTYOWATI\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://images-tm.tempo.co/all/2021/09/20/782898/782898_720.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://images-tm.tempo.co/all/2021/09/20/782899/782899_1200.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://images-tm.tempo.co/all/2021/09/20/782900/782900_1200.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://images-tm.tempo.co/all/2021/09/20/782901/782901_1200.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par \uc2 Document TEMGEN0020210920eh9k0000b\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
