\par\par \b \uc2 Analysis: Tapering without tantrum: Is it possible?\b0\par\par\uc2 982 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 September 2021\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 5\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2021 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Faisal Rachman, Mandiri, Jakarta\par \par \uc2 The \uc2 United States Federal Reserve\uc2 's plan to gear up to hawkish stance by winding down the pandemic-era easy monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has become clearer following the guidance made at the September 2021 Federal Open Market Committee (FOMC) meeting. While the meeting decided to leave the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  rate (Fed Funds Rate/FFR) unchanged at near zero and to maintain the pace of asset purchasing at the current level, the Fed has given signals to start hiking the FFR in 2022, a year faster than originally anticipated, and to soon reduce the quantitative easing pace.\par \par \uc2 The Fed suggested that the official tapering decision could be made at the November 2021 meeting at the earliest if the recovery progress keeps on track. However, at the same time, despite indicators of US \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity and employment having continued to strengthen and inflation having risen to a 13-year high, the Fed decided to revise down its 2021 \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth projection. The growth forecast was cut from 7.0 percent to 5.9 percent due to the issues of the Delta variant and supply constraints weighing down on the recovery.\par \par \uc2 The global financial market reacted quite well to the non-imminent removal of the Fed's easy-money \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Asian emerging market equity indices were closed mostly higher a day after the September 2021 FOMC meeting. In Indonesia's case, the Jakarta Composite Index (JCI) rose and booked a net foreign inflow. Moreover, the yield of the benchmark government bond reportedly fell. Some queries then arise. What will happen when the final guidance for the Fed's tapering is officially introduced? Has the market priced in the Fed's tapering agenda? Will Indonesia reexperience a taper tantrum like in 2013?\par \par \uc2 Several factors will determine these matters. The Fed's relatively dovish tone at the September 2021 meeting was highly influenced by a significant rise in COVID-19 cases amid the Delta variant. This has hampered the progress of achieving one of the Fed's monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  goals, which is maximum employment. Job gain in August 2021 was reported to markedly slow, with the slowdown concentrated in sectors most sensitive to the pandemic, such as the service sector encompassing leisure and hospitality. Caregiving needs and ongoing fears of the virus appeared to be the main factors curbing employment growth.\par \par \uc2 However, the most recent data show that the US seems to have passed the peak of the Delta surge. Vaccination in the US, furthermore, keeps progressing and is already near the herd immunity target of 70 percent of the population. Around 65 percent of the population have been given at least one dose of vaccine and around 56 percent of the population are fully vaccinated. This could allow the \uc2 US government\uc2  to keep opening the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  even further. \b \highlight22\uc2 Public\b0 \highlight\uc2  mobility in consequence will substantially increase, spurring \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. The inflation rate, along with this, could be persistent well above the 2 percent target for quite some time. There is hence still a possibility for the Fed's decision to be more hawkish in the next FOMC meeting despite \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  surrounding the pandemic. In other words, the tapering risk remains going forward.\par \par \uc2 Another risk may come from the decision of some emerging market central banks to aggressively raise the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  rate long before the Fed's agenda to hike the FFR. For 2021 year-to-date, Russia and Brazil have raised the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  rate by 250 bps and 425 bps, respectively. While Indonesia's real rate remains one of the most attractive in the market amid low inflation expectation, the inflation rate moving forward may eventually increase as the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  restrictions are progressively relaxed and demand improves.\par \par \uc2 This could diminish the attractiveness of Indonesia's financial instruments, which consequently restrains capital inflow to some degree if BI-7DRRR continues to be maintained at its lowest level ever. Thus, it is pivotal for \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to keep preemptive and ahead the curve in order to retain stability without being counterproductive to the attempt of accelerating Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery, particularly until the first half of 2022.\par \par \uc2 So, how ready is Indonesia to tackle the tapering risk? The good news is that Indonesia's external sector is now much more resilient than in 2013. Foreign \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  jumped to the highest level on record in August 2021, to US$144.8 billion. This is notably higher compared to the position in 2013, which was only $99.4 billion. The current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  (CAD) in the first half of 2021 remained low at -0.58 percent of GDP, thanks to recovery in global demand and rising commodity prices maintaining the trade balance surplus.\par \par \uc2 The CAD in 2013, meanwhile, posted a large \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of -3.19 percent of GDP. Foreign ownership in government bonds in 2021 also declined to around 22-23 percent, lower than in 2013, when it was 32.5 percent. Moreover, the inflation rate until August 2021 was still below the lower bound of the target corridor of 3?1 percent. It was much lower than 2013 inflation that hit 8 percent. The low inflation rate as a result provides a positive real rate unlike what happened in 2013 when there was a negative real rate as the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  rate was at 7.5 percent, below the inflation rate.\par \par \uc2 The exit strategy of tapering by the Fed is certain to happen, yet the success in overcoming the slight possibility of tantrum will remain depending on the synergy between \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the government in strengthening Indonesia's external sector. While monetary and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies are keys in maintaining stability and promoting \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, the vaccination program and crisis management related to the COVID-19 pandemic continue to play a very crucial role in maintaining Indonesia's financial market and instrument attractiveness in general.\par \par \uc2 _________________\par \par \uc2 Economist at Bank Mandiri\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020210928eh9t00007\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
