\par\par \b \uc2 Advertorial: Earlier financial planning helps you face tomorrow's  \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty \highlight\b0\par\par\uc2 1,512 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 October 2021\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 5\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2021 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Post,\par \par \uc2 Are you the type of person who has a habit of delaying office tasks?\par \par \uc2 As a young professional, you would probably answer, "No, I am not."\par \par \uc2 "I try not to delay my tasks because once I delay, my work will pile up, which will make me stressed and panicky because I'll have to complete the tasks simultaneously," said a 30-year-old professional at a private company, who declined to be named.\par \par \uc2 The young professional tries not to delay office related tasks due to the immediate impact on his life, in this case having to face piled up jobs, which could lead to stress.\par \par \uc2 However, when asked about financial planning for the future, the young professional fell silent, pondering over the question.\par \par \uc2 "Most Indonesian people always see things from the bright side. That's why there are common idioms such as 'untungnya' [luckily, or fortunately] that Indonesians says whenever unfortunate things happen in their life," said PT Sun Life Financial Indonesia's president director Elin Waty.\par \par \uc2 Indonesians are also used to saying "lihat aja besok" (we'll see what happens tomorrow) whenever they are asked about something in the future. "This actually shows how optimistic Indonesians are, and underlines why Indonesians have a common behavior, which is to procrastinate," she said.\par \par \uc2 Most Indonesian people tended to procrastinate over various things, including delaying their financial planning, she said.\par \par \uc2 Nowadays, the country's younger generation tends to live their lives for today where, borrowing a term that they frequently use, "you only live once". This has encouraged people to delay having a financial plan. It comes as no surprise, therefore, to learn that young people prioritize their hobbies or lifestyle trends, yet when asked about their future, they tend to delay.\par \par \uc2 "This is the mindset that we want Indonesian people to change," she said.\par \par \uc2 She explained further that because of the COVID-19 pandemic, "we have learned that life is full of risks and tomorrow is filled with \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . This is why it is important for all of us to change our mindset, that we need to prepare our lives better. It is unwise if we just focus on things that happen today, we need to start thinking and take actions for our tomorrow," she said.\par \par \uc2 Avoiding the risks\par \par \uc2 According to Elin, in life, humankind faces three potential risks at any one time: the risk of being ill - either common or critical illnesses, the risk of accident and the risk of death. "If one of these occurs, unexpected things will ensue," she said.\par \par \uc2 "For example, if one is sick, then he or she will face the risk of income reduction. Or, if someone dies unexpectedly, but he doesn't have savings, then the family he leaves will bear the risks. Don't make the family he leaves face hardships to survive," she remarked.\par \par \uc2 "We can avoid these risks if we decide to start planning our finances as early as possible. With a purpose of financial planning, we can continue our lives and continue to achieve our financial goals in the future," she said.\par \par \uc2 When people are asked about what they have done or what they have prepared for their future, the usual answer that we hear is "lihat aja nanti" (we'll see what happens later).\par \par \uc2 "So, instead of being a procrastinator, we encourage Indonesian families to start taking charge of the ones they care for, today," Sun Life's top executive said.\par \par \uc2 "As we know tomorrow is full of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , we would like to spread the message to Indonesians and ask them to start securing their tomorrow, today. 'Pastikan besokmu lebih tenang, dengan memiliki proteksi asuransi, sekarang' , or securing your tomorrow by having an insurance today."\par \par \uc2 "We want people to start prioritizing financial planning. By preparing your finances ahead of time, you can enjoy your life. Most importantly, you can enjoy your life without having to worry about any unexpected hardships that may occur tomorrow."\par \par \uc2 "So, whenever people ask you what have you done or what have you prepared for your future, you can answer confidently by saying #LihatAjaBesok!"\par \par \uc2 According to Elin, when Indonesian families start financial planning for their future, there are three key areas that they need to focus on. These three areas are mostly forgotten when preparing for the future: education funds, health and retirement.\par \par \uc2 Data from Statistics Indonesia (BPS) show that education fund inflation reaches 10 to 15 percent every year. "This is alarming, especially if you don't start preparing your children's education fund," she said.\par \par \uc2 A Global Medical Trends survey has revealed that medical costs in Indonesia are expected to rise approximately 12 percent this year. "If you don't prepare wisely, this could be dangerous as it could use up your savings or emergency fund," she said.\par \par \uc2 Only around 9 percent of society live peacefully in their retirement period, according to the Financial Institution Pension Fund (DPLK). Around 18 percent of those who are already retired need to continue working in order to fulfill their life needs. This could be well-prevented if you start planning for your retirement as early as possible.\par \par \uc2 "Given these alarming facts, it is important for Indonesians, especially the younger generation, to stop procrastinating. Start planning your future, start securing your tomorrow, today."\par \par \uc2 Credible partner\par \par \uc2 To help you with planning that suits your needs and which helps you navigate to reach your dream goals, find a partner that is credible with a long and proven history of providing services and solutions to its clients.\par \par \uc2 "Credibility means a company's reputation and strong presence in Indonesia. Sun Life is known as one of the best life insurance companies in Indonesia. It is a leading international financial service organization providing insurance, wealth and asset management solutions to individual and corporate clients."\par \par \uc2 "Sun Life has operations in a number of markets worldwide, including Canada, the United States, the United Kingdom, Ireland, Hong Kong, the Philippines, Japan, Indonesia, India, China, Australia, Singapore, Vietnam, Malaysia and Bermuda. As an additional note, \uc2 Sun Life Financial Inc\uc2  is also listed on the stock exchanges in Toronto (\uc2 TSX\uc2 ), New York (NYSE) and the Philippines (\uc2 PSE\uc2 ).\par \par \uc2 Sun Life has operated for more than 150 years worldwide. The company has faced various global crises, including World War I, The Great Depression, World War II and various world \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crises. Yet Sun Life has continued to serve millions of families around the world, including in Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 "In Indonesia, Sun Life started its operation in 1995, which means it has been operating for more than 25 years. Sun Life offers various protection solutions that are designed to meet the client's purpose. Our commitment in Indonesia is to help families achieve their financial security, and live healthier lives," Elin said.\par \par \uc2 Other factors that families should put into consideration, is a company's financial performance, and its risk-based capital.\par \par \uc2 Indonesia's Financial Services Authority\uc2  (OJK), requires a company to fulfill its minimum responsible business conduct (RBC) of 120 percent for Conventional and Syariah insurance businesses.\par \par \uc2 "The focus for life insurance businesses is trust. And to be able to trust a company, you should know the strength of a company, its credibility, its services and many other things. Once you know that a company is credible, then you can be worry-free and continue enjoying life," she pointed out.\par \par \uc2 "At Sun Life, we put clients at the center of what we do. Which means we are always committed to providing what is best for our clients. We understand that every client is unique and has different financial goals. That is why we are constantly innovating to offer new solutions that enable our clients to reach their goals.\par \par \uc2 "One of the key factors why Sun Life has been present for more than 150 years is because of our client's continuous trust. We appreciate that our clients have chosen Sun Life to be their partner to help them achieve their financial goals.\par \par \uc2 Our client's continuous trust has fueled us to be stronger each year," she explained.\par \par \uc2 "Trust from our customers continues to affirm Sun Life's commitment to realizing its mission in Indonesia to help Indonesian families achieve financial security and live healthier," she remarked.\par \par \uc2 In carrying out its obligation as a corporate citizen, Sun Life also continues to support government programs through the OJK routinely, by organizing educational programs and financial literacy to various segments of society.\par \par \uc2 "The goal is to encourage more people to understand financial planning, so that at the end of the day, they decide not to procrastinate any more. As people increasingly understand that tomorrow is full of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , it will encourage them to place financial planning as a top priority to face tomorrow. Besok Pasti, Pasti Sun Life! (Secure your tomorrow, today with Sun Life)," Elin concluded.\par \par \uc2 A week later, the young professional who had been pondering over the question of financial planning decided to purchase a life insurance \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  for himself and his family members as it gives him peace of mind.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020211017ehai00003\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
