\par\par \uc2 INTERNATIONAL NEWS\par \b \uc2 MEKONG INSTITUTE RECEIVES ASEAN PRIZE 2021\b0\par\par\uc2 587 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 October 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Yuni Arisandy Sinaga\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - The ASEAN Prize 2021 was bestowed on Mekong Institute in recognition of its contributions in promoting ASEAN awareness and bolstering regional cooperation towards sustainable development, the ASEAN Secretariat announced.\par \par \uc2 The announcement was made at the 38th and 39th ASEAN Summits, according to a release issued by the ASEAN Secretariat and received here on Friday.\par \par \uc2 The role of the ASEAN Prize in promoting \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  awareness on the core values and principles of ASEAN based on the ASEAN Charter was recognized by the ASEAN Leaders at the 38th and 39th ASEAN Summit, chaired by the Sultan of Brunei \uc2 Hassanal Bolkiah\uc2  on October 26, 2021.\par \par \uc2 In the Chairman\u8217\'20\'19s Statement issued, ASEAN leaders congratulated Mekong Institute, a research institute and community development centre based in Khon Kaen, Thailand, as recipient of the ASEAN Prize 2021, recognizing its work in promoting prosperous and harmonious sub-regional development and its contribution to a wider regional cooperation and integration, particularly in agricultural development and commercialization.\par \par \uc2 In his congratulatory remarks, Secretary-General of ASEAN Lim Jock Hoi acknowledged Mekong Institute\u8217\'20\'19s aspirations of fostering sustainable development and efforts in creating pivotal strength and being a driving force for regional \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, especially for mainland ASEAN.\par \par \uc2 "Their key role in community development and capacity building, publication as well as research and training programmes have helped bridge the gap in the region and accelerate equitable growth towards an inclusive, cohesive, and prosperous ASEAN Community," Lim affirmed.\par \par \uc2 "The ASEAN appreciates Mekong Institute\u8217\'20\'19s 25 years of dedication towards realizing this objective and hopes the prize will encourage and support their work going forward," he stated.\par \par \uc2 Mekong Institute Executive Director Suriyan Vichitlekarn stated that the prize was received with great honor on behalf of those who have tirelessly advanced GMS development and cooperation for a stronger ASEAN.\par \par \uc2 He emphasized that the recognition strengthens Mekong Institute\u8217\'20\'19s resolve to work even harder in empowering people, bridging partnerships, and advocating positive change, especially during these \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  times.\par \par \uc2 "Mekong Institute remains a steadfast partner in helping people emerge safely from the pandemic, so they may thrive in the new normal, wherein new levels of growth, trust, well-being, and a deeper sense of belonging will endure for many years to come," he stated.\par \par \uc2 The ASEAN Prize is an annual regional premier award, administered by the ASEAN Secretariat, honoring individuals or organizations based in ASEAN that have demonstrated outstanding work, with significant contribution to community-building efforts.\par \par \uc2 The recipient will receive a trophy and a cash prize of US$20,000 sponsored by the Temasek Foundation of Singapore and Yayasan Hasanah of Malaysia.\par \par \uc2 Following the COVID-19 safety protocols, the 2021 award presentation will be conducted separately. The year 2021 marks the fourth edition of the ASEAN Prize.\par \par \uc2 Founded in 1996 and based in Khon Kaen, Thailand, Mekong Institute\u8217\'20\'19s commitment to promoting ASEAN Community building has been continuously articulated through a range of capacity development programs, research studies, publications, and multi-institutional engagements.\par \par \uc2 The intergovernmental organization has become a guiding beacon in advancing regional cooperation and integration, particularly in responding to priority needs of the Greater Mekong Subregion (GMS).\par \par \uc2 It implements cross-sectoral projects in agricultural development and commercialization, trade and investment facilitation, and sustainable energy and environment, thereby reflecting the immense support to the core tenets of the \uc2 ASEAN \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Community\uc2  (\uc2 AEC\uc2 ) and the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (UN SDG) 2030 vision.\par \par \uc2 (T.Y012/A/H-FDH/H-FDH) 29-10-2021 14:28:56\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020211029ehat000b5\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
