75 of the Mining Law that stipulates state-owned miners should be given priority over special mining permits.\par \par \uc2 Citing the same article, the court also said that private companies should bid for special mining permits.\par \par \uc2 The court decision strengthens the government's grip over the domestic mining industry in line with the country's growing resource nationalism, a key principle in the Mining Law.\par \par \uc2 State-owned miners such as tin miner \uc2 PT Timah\uc2  and gold and nickel miner \uc2 PT Aneka Tambang\uc2  (Antam) are already among the biggest in their industries. Meanwhile, state-owned mining holding firm MIND ID has acquired big stakes in top gold miner \uc2 PT Freeport Indonesia\uc2  and nickel miner \uc2 PT Vale Indonesia\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 MIND ID SVP corporate secretary Ratih Amri told The Jakarta Post on Thursday that the court's decision would not have any significant immediate impact on MIND ID Group operations, as a majority of the company's permits were of the mining operation permit (IUP) type or already of the IUPK type.\par \par \uc2 "MIND ID supports the government's endeavors to attract investments and create a conducive regulatory climate in the coal industry going forward," she said.\par \par \uc2 Indonesian Coal Mining Association (APBI) executive director Hendra Sinadia said that the regulatory change would not affect coal mining investments.\par \par \uc2 "We believe that the government will continue to support businesses' continuity," he said in a phone call on Tuesday.\par \par \uc2 Hendra added that, as long as companies complied with the laws and regulations stipulated in their contracts, they would still be considered for an extension.\par \par \uc2 As of September, mining industry investments reached only 62.7 percent of the total US$4.3 billion target for the year, as a result of regulatory \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , according to the Energy and Mineral Resources Ministry.\par \par \uc2 Concurring with the APBI, Bisman Bhaktiar, executive director of the Center for Energy and Mining Law (Pushep), told the Post on Tuesday that the decision would not affect investments in the downstream mineral and coal industry.\par \par \uc2 He suggested that SOEs participate in cooperation schemes with private companies or contract holders.\par \par \uc2 "Such cooperation would be more fair and proportional," he said, adding that decisions relating to contract extensions should be made in a transparent and accountable manner.\par \par \uc2 Contrary to Pushep and the APBI, Indonesian Mining Experts Association (Perhapi) chairman Rizal Kasli said that the court decision might disrupt investment and business development plans, but also improve the government's evaluation process of businesses.\par \par \uc2 "The new \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  may cause IUPK issuance to take longer, thereby affecting investors' rates of return on investment and business development plans, including exploration projects," he said.\par \par \uc2 Rizal suggested the government extend the mining license to more than 20 years to incentivize exploration.\par \par \uc2 Febrianti Nadira, corporate communication head at coal mining giant \uc2 PT Adaro Energy\uc2 , said the company would comply with the government's decision.\par \par \uc2 "Adaro hopes regulations in the coal industry will enable national companies to exist and support national energy security," she told the Post on Tuesday.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020211105ehb600003\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
