\par\par \uc2 NATIONAL NEWS\par \b \uc2 SUCCESSFUL PANDEMIC CONTROL IS KEY TO 2022  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMIC \highlight\uc2  GROWTH: PRESIDENT\b0\par\par\uc2 434 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 November 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - President \uc2 Joko Widodo\uc2  (Jokowi) believes that the key to \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in 2022 primarily lay in the success in controlling the COVID-19 pandemic amid the problems still riddling the world.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CWe all have to take precautionary measures. We must prepare ourselves and (we must) be careful but also not overly paranoid. The most important aspect in my opinion is that there is only one key to \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  (growth) in 2022, which is to control what is called COVID-19," President Jokowi affirmed here on Thursday.\par \par \uc2 The head of state elaborated that for the year 2022, there are lingering \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , doubts, and complexity of issues related to climate change, the likelihood of a spike in global inflation, global supply chain constraints, and a decrease in the quantity of asset purchases in the financial market by the US \b \highlight22\uc2 Central Bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , The Fed.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CClimate change is feared to lead to a food crisis. All countries are now also concerned because inflation in all countries is rising, and the people are also afraid of a tapering off," he noted while adding that the world was currently also facing logistical problems, with goods containers idling on global supply chain routes.\par \par \uc2 According to the president, the incidents now and in the future are the outcome of disruption that complicated the world"s problems.\par \par \uc2 Thus, Indonesia must prepare itself to face the era of disruption that alters the world order. Preparations must be made judiciously, but one should steer clear from being overly concerned, even to the point of fear or paranoia.\par \par \uc2 Jokowi deemed the success in controlling COVID-19 as the most important key to facing various challenges.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CThe key is just that. If we cannot control it (the COVID-19 pandemic), the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will decline, fall yet again. I think the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of other countries is experiencing the first, second, and third (COVID-19) waves, (not to mention) the fourth. This is why, (I) once again (remind you to) be careful and (exercise) vigilance," Jokowi stressed.\par \par \uc2 The president is targeting to increase Indonesia"s resilience to the COVID-19 pandemic, with the hopes that the national daily COVID-19 cases would continue to decline and that the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  will remain disciplined in following health protocols and get vaccinated.\par \par \uc2 The government targets an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth at 5.0-5.5 percent in the 2022 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  Law or better than the 2021 projection pegged at 3.7-4.5 percent.\par \par \uc2 (T.KR-MCA/A/H-FDH/H-FDH) 18-11-2021 16:31:45\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020211118ehbi000ul\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
