\par\par \b \uc2 In for flexible labor market\b0\par\par\uc2 548 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 November 2021\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2021 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Post,\par \par \uc2 Trade union leaders should understandably be disillusioned by the1.09 percent increase in provincial minimum labor wages set by the Manpower Ministry for 2022,as it is far below the range of the 7 to 10 percent rise they had demanded. But they should not lose sight of the big picture of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which contracted by 2.1 percent last year and is expected to grow by only 3.2 to 3.5 percent this year amidcontinued \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  brought on by the pandemic.\par \par \uc2 Even though provincial and regency administrations are still authorized to increase the minimum wage under certain conditions to a higher rate than the national average fixed by the government, regional leaders are well-advised to realize that the tiny wage rise was set after several months of consultations within the national wage council and with the representatives of trade union federations and industrial associations.\par \par \uc2 We fully support the workers' demand that the compulsory minimum wage support at least the basic cost of living for workers to sustain a decent livelihood, especially because the government decided in 2020 not to raise the minimum wage because of thedevastating impacts of the health crisis.\par \par \uc2 But the blunt fact is that the pandemic has been damaging contact-sensitive sectors such as travel, transportation, manufacturing, trading andhospitality, causing massive worker layoffs. Many enterprises are able to continue operating only after the \uc2 Financial Services Authority (OJK) \uc2 extended to the end of March 2023 a loan restructuring relaxation facility as a countercyclical \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to cushion borrowers from the impact of the virus infection.\par \par \uc2 Wage rises are not sustainable if revenues do not increase either by higher productivity or bigger market sales. In fact, data showed that Indonesian minimum wages had increased at an 8 percent compound annual growth rate over five years to 2019 (before the pandemic) despite real gross domestic product (GDP) growth of only 5 percent.\par \par \uc2 When we talk about labor economics, we should not focus only on the minimum wage. Next year will usher in the full-fledged implementation of bold labor reforms under the 2020 Job Creation Law and Government \b \highlight22\uc2 Regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  No. 36/2021, which make the labor market more flexible in terms of a better, fixed formula for determining an annual minimum labor wage, contract workers and decreased severance costs.\par \par \uc2 But the new rules also provide unemployment insurance for workers and add the factors of household \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  and unemployment rate into the calculation of wages.\par \par \uc2 A more flexible labor market is necessary to ensure that structural transformation strengthens \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, especially amid the expansion of the digital \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . We should note that only about 35 percent of the estimated 140 million workerswould benefit from the mandated minimum wage because the other 65 percent remain trapped in the informal \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Even though the core unemployment rate is estimated at only 7 percent,tens of millions are still under-employed. Too-rigid labor rules in the past have hindered investments to create jobs.\par \par \uc2 However, given the weak bargaining position of workers while employees' and employers' demands are conflicting in dealing with matters of job security, welfare and social protection, it is most imperative for the government to strengthen labor inspections to ensure that the new labor rules are properly enforced.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020211118ehbj00003\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
