\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b \uc2 BI RECORDS SURPLUS OF US$10.7 BILLION IN BALANCE OF PAYMENTS\b0\par\par\uc2 505 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 November 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Azis Kurmala\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) \uc2 recorded a surplus of US$10.7 billion in the balance of payments (BOP) in the third quarter of 2021 after experiencing a \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of US$0.4 billion in the previous quarter.\par \par \uc2 "Thus, this supports external resilience," Head of BI"s Communication Department, Erwin Haryono, noted in an official statement received in Jakarta on Friday.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  at the end of September 2021 reached US$146.9 billion, higher than US$137.1 billion at the end of June 2021.\par \par \uc2 The foreign exchange reserve position is equivalent to financing 8.6 months of imports and servicing government external debt, as it is above the international adequacy standards.\par \par \uc2 In the third quarter of 2021, the current account recorded a surplus that was mainly supported by a significant increase in the balance of trade (goods) surplus.\par \par \uc2 The current account in the reporting period recorded a surplus of US$4.5 billion (1.5 percent of the GDP) after a \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of US$2.0 billion (0.7 percent of the GDP) during the previous quarter.\par \par \uc2 A surplus in the goods balance drove this positive performance due to an increase in non-oil and gas exports that aligned with strong demand from trading partner countries and the continued increase in prices of major export commodities in the international market.\par \par \uc2 On the other hand, the services account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  was lower, partly due to improved performance in transportation services and supported by increased revenue from freight services as export activity improved.\par \par \uc2 The primary income account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  increased on account of an increase in payments for direct investment returns, influenced by improvements in the performance of natural resource-based corporations.\par \par \uc2 The capital and financial account in the third quarter of 2021 recorded a surplus of US$6.1 billion (two percent of the GDP), higher than the US$1.6 billion (0.6 percent of the GDP) in the previous quarter.\par \par \uc2 "This is increasing, especially from direct investment. Net inflows of direct investment are maintained at US$3.3 billion," Haryono affirmed.\par \par \uc2 Other investments also recorded a surplus after experiencing a \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the previous quarter as influenced by a decrease in net foreign loan payments, an increase in the placement of non-resident deposits in the country, and an additional allocation of special drawing rights (SDR).\par \par \uc2 Portfolio investment during the third quarter of 2021 also recorded net inflows of US$1.1 billion, although it decreased, from US$4.0 billion in the previous quarter in line with the global financial market \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Haryono ensured that BI will continually monitor the dynamics of the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  that could affect the outlook for the balance of payments.\par \par \uc2 BI also continued to strengthen the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  mix to maintain \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability and continued \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  coordination with the government and relevant authorities to strengthen external sector resilience, he added.\par \par \uc2 (T.A063/A/R013/R013) 19-11-2021 19:46:04\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020211119ehbj001rx\par }\p