\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b \uc2 FITCH AFFIRMS INDONESIA'S CREDIT RATING WITH STABLE OUTLOOK\b0\par\par\uc2 450 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 November 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - Credit rating agency Fitch affirmed Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s sovereign credit rating at BBB (investment grade) with a stable outlook on November 22, 2021, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) \uc2 reported.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CThe affirmation of Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s rating at BBB with stable outlook reflects recognition from Fitch, as one of the world\u8217\'20\'19s leading credit rating agencies, over the macroeconomic stability and financial system of Indonesia that remain manageable,\u8221\'20\'1D BI Governor \uc2 Perry Warjiyo\uc2  said in a written statement released on Tuesday.\par \par \uc2 In addition, it also indicates strong prospects for the domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the medium term amid uneven global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  about the global financial market, he added.\par \par \uc2 The strong prospects for the domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  are inseparable from credible \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and synergy between the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the government in the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  mix, he said.\par \par \uc2 Looking ahead, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  will keep observing global and domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  developments, take the necessary steps to ensure macroeconomic stability and financial system, and synergize with the government to expedite national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery, Warjiyo said.\par \par \uc2 Fitch\u8217\'20\'19s affirmation of Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s credit rating is based on good prospects for the nation"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the medium term and the low ratio of the government\u8217\'20\'19s debts to the national gross domestic product (GDP), he informed.\par \par \uc2 However, Fitch has highlighted several challenges that may cast a shadow on the nation"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  prospects, including high dependence on external financing, low government revenues, and several structural features, such as per capita GDP and governance indicators lagging behind other countries that have the same rating, he pointed out.\par \par \uc2 With a decline in COVID-19 cases after a spike in June-August 2021, Fitch has seen potential for the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to grow higher than the previous forecast of 3.2 percent given the improving mobility of the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the high prices of export commodities, he said.\par \par \uc2 Fitch has forecast the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will expand by 6.8 percent in 2022 and continue to grow by 6 percent in the succeeding years due to the positive impact of the Job Creation Law on rising investment, he added.\par \par \uc2 On the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  side, Fitch has expressed the hope that the implementation of harmonized \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  laws will help the government in returning the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  to below 3 percent of the GDP in 2023, he noted.\par \par \uc2 Thus, the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  is projected to reach 5.4 percent in 2021 and decline further to 4.5 percent in 2022, lower than the government-set target of 5.8 percent in 2021 and 4.9 percent in 2022, he added.\par \par \uc2 (T.H-SHT/A/R013/R013) 23-11-2021 19:20:05\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0