\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia \highlight\uc2  Governor Outlines 5 Global  \highlight22\uc2 Economic \highlight\uc2  Challenges Next Year\b0\par\par\uc2 300 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 November 2021\par \uc2 Tempo.co\par \uc2 TEMPOE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk \par \par \uc2 TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - Governor of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) \uc2 Perry Warjiyo\uc2  predicted that the progress of global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery next year will be more balanced. It is evident from the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery in a number of European countries and Japan following the United States.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile in emerging markets, the economies of India and ASEAN-5 are starting to catch up with China. This is supported by the declining COVID-19 cases, the reopening of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  sector, and the continued \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  for \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary policies.\par \par \uc2 However, Perry opined that there are five challenges in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery at the global level. The first challenge is the normalization of monetary and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies in developed countries, as well as lingering \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in global financial markets.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CSecondly, the pandemic impacts on corporations and financial system stability. The third is the spread of inter-country digital payment systems and the risk of crypto assets,\u8221\'20\'1D he explained at the BI\u8217\'20\'19s annual meeting today, November 24.\par \par \uc2 The fourth challenge is the demand of a green financial \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and the last one is the widening gap and needs for financial inclusion.\par \par \uc2 However, Perry expressed optimism that Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will continue to recover with a 4.7-5.5 percent growth in 2022. \u8220\'20\'1COther than exports, the consumption and investment will increase, supported by vaccinations, reopening of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  sector, and \b \highlight22\uc2 policy stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2 ,\u8221\'20\'1D he added.\par \par \uc2 Perry was also optimistic that the next year\u8217\'20\'19s inflation will be under control at the range of 2-4 percent. \u8220\'20\'1CThe stability of the rupiah exchange rate will be maintained, given \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s strong commitment amid the Fed\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  normalization.\par \par \uc2 Read: Sri Mulyani Upbeat \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Recovery to Strengthen in Q4 2021\par \par \uc2 BISNIS.COM\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://statik.tempo.co/data/2020/03/11/id_922365/922365_720.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par \uc2 Document TEMPOE0020211124ehbo000ma\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
