\par\par \uc2 NATIONAL NEWS\par \b \uc2 INDONESIA MUST PREPARE ANTICIPATORY MEASURES AGAINST OMICRON VARIANT SOON: WIDODO\b0\par\par\uc2 395 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 November 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - Indonesia must implement policies for anticipating and mitigating the new variant of the coronavirus called Omicron, or B.1.1.529, as early as possible, President \uc2 Joko Widodo\uc2  (Jokowi) has said.\par \par \uc2 The mitigation must be taken seriously to support the structural reform program and national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery, he added.\par \par \uc2 "The Omicron variant has emerged and we must increase our vigilance. Anticipation and mitigation need to be prepared as early as possible," Widodo remarked during the submission of the \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  Allocation List (DIPA) and the 2022 Book of Allocations for Fund Transfers to Regions and Villages in a meeting at the State Palace on Monday.\par \par \uc2 He asked the ranks of the central and regional governments to remain vigilant, saying the COVID-19 pandemic has not ended yet. The spread of the coronavirus still remains a threat to the world, including Indonesia, he added.\par \par \uc2 The 2022 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  (APBN) has been prepared as a \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  instrument that is responsive, anticipatory, and flexible to help the nation face the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  of the pandemic, he emphasized. The 2022 APBN also accommodates several innovations and anticipates various changes that can occur, with good financial and administrative governance, he added.\par \par \uc2 In addition, the President said that the 2022 APBN also seeks to revive the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and continue the structural reform agenda.\par 