\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMIC \highlight\uc2  RECOVERY TO BE ACCOMPANIED BY NEW RISKS: MINISTER\b0\par\par\uc2 464 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 November 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Azis Kurmala\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery in 2022 will be accompanied by the emergence of new risks, such as commodity price volatility in global markets, inflationary pressures that could have an impact on rising \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and geopolitical dynamics. Finance Minister \uc2 Sri Mulyani Indrawati\uc2  made the statement at the State Palace, Jakarta, on Monday during the submission of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  execution lists (DIPA) and the list of transfer allocations to regions and village funds in 2022.\par \par \uc2 The new risks must be managed so as not to disrupt the pace of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery and structural reforms, she added.\par \par \uc2 "The \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery in 2022 will be accompanied by the emergence of new risks that must be managed, such as commodity price volatility; inflationary pressures and the implications of rising \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  in developed countries, especially the United States; China"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  rebalancing; as well as supply chain disruptions and geopolitical dynamics," she said.\par \par \uc2 According to Indrawati, global and domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery in 2022 will still remain uneven and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 . This is mainly due to the dynamics of the COVID-19 pandemic, which continues to be overshadowed by the emergence of new variants of the coronavirus, such as the B.1.1.529, or Omicron, variant.\par \par \uc2 She expected that the handling of the spread of the COVID-19, which proved effective some time ago, could be a strategy for Indonesia to prevent the transmission of new variants. This must be accompanied by the acceleration of COVID-19 vaccinations to create community immunity so that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities can resume, she added.\par \par \uc2 "The success of the Indonesian government in controlling the Delta variant and maintaining vigilance and discipline in health protocols is expected to be a strong provision in dealing with the new threat of the new Omicron variant," the Finance Minister said.\par \par \uc2 Regarding the 2022 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  (APBN), she emphasized that the government"s \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  instruments are still expansive and accommodate counter-cyclical policies, but still pay attention to risks, and prioritize \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  sustainability in the medium and long term.\par \par \uc2 The government is targeting a State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of 4.85 percent of the gross domestic product, or Rp868 trillion, in 2022, she noted. The \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  is narrower compared to the 2021 outlook of 5.2\u8211\'20\'135.4 percent of the GDP.\par \par \uc2 The APBN \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  will result from the ceiling on state revenue of Rp1,846.1 trillion and state \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Rp2,714.2 trillion, she said. With this \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  posture, the government is targeting \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of 5.2 percent in 2022, compared to the outlook for 2021, which is pegged at 3.5\u8211\'20\'134 percent. (INE)\par \par \uc2 EDITED BY INE\par \par \uc2 (T.A063/A/H-FDH/H-FDH) 29-11-2021 23:08:30\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020211129ehbt001xh\par