\par\par \b \uc2 Omicron variant casts shadow over RI's  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  recovery\b0\par\par\uc2 Vincent Fabian Thomas, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \uc2 878 \uc2 words\par \uc2 2 December 2021\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 1\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2021 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Government officials are on high alert over the more transmissible Omicron variant of COVID-19, which has rekindled concerns of fresh mobility restrictions and greater relief \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , possibly spoiling Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery plans for next year.\par \par \uc2 So far, officials and economists do not expect the Omicron variant to have a major impact on the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , citing the country's limited room for emergency response measures and its preparedness after dealing with two COVID-19 waves.\par \par \uc2 Economists specifically expect the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  impact to be nowhere as bad as 2020, but they also say things could go south, depending on what medical experts learn about the new variant and how other governments respond over the coming months.\par \par \uc2 President Joko "Jokowi" Widodo instructed his Cabinet on Monday to be on alert over the Omicron variant and to design the 2022 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  to be "responsive, adaptive and flexible in the face of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  ahead".\par \par \uc2 "We must be more vigilant with the new Omicron variant present. Mitigations should be prepared as early as possible so it will not disrupt the structural reform and national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery that we are doing," he said.\par \par \uc2 The President last month broached a prolonged pandemic as one of several key macroeconomic risks that the government was anticipating in 2022. Other risks included the \uc2 United States Federal Reserve\uc2 's tapering, slowing Chinese \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and falling commodity prices.\par \par \uc2 The \uc2 World Health Organization\uc2  recently classified the Omicron variant as "very high risk" with a high chance of spreading across borders and estimated it would take another two weeks to fully understand it. Many countries, including Indonesia, have imposed travel bans to try to keep out the new variant.\par \par \uc2 Finance Minister \uc2 Sri Mulyani Indrawati\uc2  reaffirmed on Tuesday that the government was confident about achieving \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery in 2022 because business activity had largely resumed following the successful handling of the Delta wave, but regulators would nevertheless be "very vigilant" over the spread of COVID-19, including the Omicron variant.\par \par \uc2 "Despite facing the dynamics of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in 2022 is projected to continue its recovery to become stronger," she said.\par \par \uc2 Indonesia expects its \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to largely return to pre-pandemic conditions by 2022 as indicated by a gross domestic product (GDP) growth target of 5.5 percent outlined in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , compared to the 4.5 percent expected this year and negative 2.07 percent recorded last year, during the height of the pandemic.\par \par \uc2 The Finance Ministry plans to be more prudent over government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  next year by tightening aid recipients and by timing bonds issuance according to global market dynamics.\par \par \uc2 Fikri C. Permana, a senior economist at Samuel Sekuritas, expects the government to reimpose some degree of activity restrictions to mitigate infection risks, but the effect on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would not be as severe as the impact of the Delta variant outbreak, as the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  has adapted to living under such curbs.\par \par \uc2 Indonesia's GDP grew 3.51 percent in the third quarter, below the government expectation of 4.5 percent.\par \par \uc2 GDP will be bolstered by exports, which is expected to remain strong next year due to high commodity prices, also allowing the country to bank on foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  to shield the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  from the Fed taper, said Fikri.\par \par \uc2 However, the Constitutional Court's recent ruling against the Job Creation Law was expected to create legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  that would negatively impact investors' appetite, hampering investment inflows, especially foreign direct investments, for the next two years, he said.\par \par \uc2 "The risk from new variants, including Omicron, will be minimal. There will be a downside risk but it won't be as big as last July or August," Fikri told The Jakarta Post on Tuesday.\par \par \uc2 Similarly, \uc2 Fitch Ratings\uc2  said on Monday that "another large, synchronized global downturn, such as that seen in the first half of last year, is highly unlikely".\par \par \uc2 The credit rating agency said it was unlikely for governments to impose stringent lockdowns due to the higher political bars over them and the rollout of vaccination programs, which reduced countries' reliance on non-pharmaceutical interventions (NPIs) to contain the pandemic.\par \par \uc2 Fitch Ratings\uc2  also noted that rising inflation around the world would make it difficult for central banks to loosen their monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 In Indonesia, where inflation remains below target, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) \uc2 can afford to hold its benchmark seven-day reverse repo rate (7DRRR) at 3.5 percent this month, the lowest level since the rate was introduced in 2016.\par \par \uc2 Private lender Bank Permata economist Josua Pardede said on Tuesday that a spread of the Omicron variant would pinch the government as it would have to raise relief \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , especially in health care and social aid, but prevailing regulations required returning the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  to below 3 percent of GDP by 2023.\par \par \uc2 Furthermore, bond issuance costs were expected to rise next year due to the Fed's taper, making it more expensive to finance higher \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  through debt.\par \par \uc2 "We hope the government can be more preventive [in containing COVID-19], so it won't have to resort to \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity restrictions or widen the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  because of increased \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  for pandemic response," Josua told the Post.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020211201ehc20000a\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
