\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b \uc2 PANDEMIC LEAVES COMPLEX CHALLENGES:  \highlight22\uc2 BANK INDONESIA \highlight\uc2 'S GOVERNOR\b0\par\par\uc2 305 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 December 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - The COVID-19 pandemic that has protracted for almost two years worldwide has thrown various complex challenges at Indonesia and the world despite recovery of the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 "s Governor \uc2 Perry Warjiyo\uc2  stated.\par \par \uc2 "For almost two years, we have learnt a lot about how to solve very complex problems arising from this pandemic," Warjiyo noted at the \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Book Launch & Research Expo online event here on Monday.\par \par \uc2 To this end, the governor noted that such challenges will be discussed within the scope of the six agendas of the Indonesia"s G20 Presidency finance track in 2022.\par \par \uc2 The first of these agendas is how to normalize \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary policies that could support a balanced global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  without triggering \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the financial market.\par \par \uc2 The second agenda is how to handle the scaring effects of the pandemic on corporations, including Micro, Small, and Medium Enterprises (MSMEs).\par \par \uc2 The third concerns the issue of digitalization of the financial \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , including the payment system.\par \par \uc2 The fourth agenda is green \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and finance, while the fifth pertains to \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and financial inclusion. The last agenda concerns international \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "These are global and national problems that require prompt answers from policies based on conceptual, theoretical, and empirical thinking," Warjiyo affirmed.\par \par \uc2 In addition, BI unveiled two books titled: \b \highlight22\uc2 Central Bank Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Mix: Issues, Challenges and \b \highlight22\uc2 Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Responses as well as Periphery and Small Ones Matter: Interplay of \b \highlight22\uc2 Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Social Capital.\par \par \uc2 The launch mirrors support to developing science in addressing various problems arising due to the COVID-19 pandemic.\par \par \uc2 "This unveiling proves that BI is a scientific development institution, and this is our form of dedication to the nation," the BI governor asserted.\par \par \uc2 (T.KR-FLI/B/H-FDH/H-FDH) 13-12-2021 18:37:25\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020211213ehcd000ul\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
