\par\par \b \uc2 Analysis: Accelerated  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  recovery drives 2022 investment\b0\par\par\uc2 1,008 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 December 2021\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 4\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2021 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Reny Eka Putri, Mandiri, Jakarta\par \par \uc2 The mobility of the global community is starting to show an increase, following the trend of a rising Manufacturing and Services Purchasing Managers' Index (PMI), especially in the United States and China. At the same time, consumer and business confidence has also begun to improve in the \uc2 European Union\uc2 , even though it was recently hit by another wave of the pandemic.\par \par \uc2 Toward 2022, the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery is expected to continue. This has been confirmed by various early indicators that improved in November, such as the performance of the manufacturing sector, consumer confidence, as well as improved retail sales, including high demand for energy-based commodities.\par \par \uc2 Yet, the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery is also overshadowed by increasing \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  on global financial markets due to the risk of the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  normalization and the risk of stagflation. Based on \uc2 International Monetary Fund\uc2  projections, world \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is estimated to grow by 4.9 percent in 2022.\par \par \uc2 At the beginning of the pandemic, in an effort to stimulate the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and to contain the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic, central banks in a number of countries implemented monetary easing policies by cutting \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  and implementing accommodative policies.\par \par \uc2 Now, as the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  continues to recover, global central banks are expected to begin normalizing these policies. Just recently, the \uc2 US Federal Reserve\uc2  began normalization by starting the tapering of its quantitative-easing \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The Fed will then begin to make adjustments to its \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  when the US inflation rate is consistently above 2 percent and the unemployment rate continues to decline. Market participants are closely monitoring the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  changes that may be carried out by the Fed.\par \par \uc2 The improvement in the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will also affect the recovery of the domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . In terms of fundamentals, at the end of 2021, improvements in a number of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  indicators have supported a rebound in market confidence.\par \par \uc2 This is supported by a decline in new cases of COVID-19 with the successful national implementation of vaccinations and health protocols. After the government eased the multi-tiered mobility restrictions (PPKM), \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity resumed and the real sector rebounded.\par \par \uc2 The recovery may continue into 2022. \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) \uc2 predicts Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in 2022 will reach 4.7-5.5 percent from 3.2-4 percent in 2021.\par \par \uc2 This \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth will be mainly driven by the export performance, which has remained strong due to high commodity prices. The trade surplus should continue and will support improvements in consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  and investment in line with rising domestic demand. \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity will also be supported by increased mobility in line with accelerated vaccination, the opening of wider \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  sectors and continued \b \highlight22\uc2 policy stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 From the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's perspective, several \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  instruments in 2022 will be directed at accelerating the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery.\par \par \uc2 First, macroprudential policies to encourage credit and financing in priority sectors and micro, small and medium enterprises (MSMEs).\par \par \uc2 Second, accelerating the digital \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and finance through industrial consolidation, the development of modern payment system infrastructure and the digitalization of regional government financial transactions, as well as digitalizing MSMEs and tourism.\par \par \uc2 Third, money market development policies are being pursued to strengthen the effectiveness of \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  transmission, development of modern and international standard money-market infrastructure, and fourth, inclusive \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 -financial development programs for MSMEs and Islamic finance-economics.\par \par \uc2 These policies are expected to encourage market participants to be able to take advantage of the strengthening momentum.\par \par \uc2 We estimate that the process of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery will continue, thus inviting more consistent flows of foreign funds into the domestic market. The fundamentals of the domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  are relatively well maintained, supported by government and household \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  and driven by prudent monetary and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies. \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery in other countries should improve confidence and positively affect the risk appetite of global investors.\par \par \uc2 Furthermore, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is also correlated with the opening of investment opportunities. In the future, to attract investment, Indonesia will focus on developing its downstream commodity sector and accelerate digitalization to achieve more sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. From a sectoral perspective, the Investment Ministry will target priority investment sectors, which include the tourism, renewable energy, infrastructure, manufacturing and mining sectors.\par \par \uc2 In addition, three other sectors will be encouraged, namely, downstream natural resources, the green \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the digital \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . For the digital \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , it is necessary to increase the ecosystem, literacy and digitization of MSMEs. The Investment Ministry is aiming for a realization of investment worth Rp 1.2 quadrillion (US$83.7 billion) in 2022.\par \par \uc2 The ministry is also developing an administrative portal that facilitates business licensing, the aim of which is to increase competence and competitiveness. This optimism is also due to the achievement of the investment target, which in the first nine months of 2021 achieved 73 percent of the target with a balanced proportion between foreign and domestic investment.\par \par \uc2 In the January-September 2021 period, Indonesia's investment realization was recorded at Rp 659.4 trillion. This realization value grew by 7.8 percent year-on-year compared with the same period in 2020, which was Rp 611.6 trillion.\par \par \uc2 Investment performance will continue to move up in line with the recovery in community activities and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity. The government will continue to provide support through policies and implementation for both the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  and private sector. The 2022 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  will continue to focus on health support, social protection and reform policies such as human resources, MSMEs and digitalization.\par \par \uc2 In order to support \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery and inviting potential investment, Bank Mandiri Group will hold the Mandiri Investment Forum (MIF) 2022: Recapturing the Growth Momentum, on Feb. 9, 2022. MIF 2022 is part of Mandiri Group's contribution to support Indonesia's faster \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. The conference will explore policies and strategies to maintain stability and promote growth and investment.\par \par \uc2 With the ongoing \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms, this international event will also provide current updates on the issue of digitalization and environmental, social and governance (ESG) policies.\par \par \uc2 _______________\par \par \uc2 Analyst at Bank Mandiri\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020211214ehcf0000h\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
