\par\par \b \uc2 Minister \uc2 Airlangga Hartarto\uc2  Expresses Positive Outlook for the  \highlight22\uc2 Economy \highlight\b0\par\par\uc2 376 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 December 2021\par \uc2 Tempo.co\par \uc2 TEMPOE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk \par \par \uc2 TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs Airlangga Hartarto, stated that pandemic control and accommodative policies are key to maintaining the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery momentum.\par \par \uc2 "\b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth highly depends on pandemic control. The government together with all parties must help each other in controlling Covid-19 to continue to drive national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery," Airlangga said in his statement in Jakarta on Friday, December 17, 2021.\par \par \uc2 Airlangga said that the government is optimistic that Indonesia will be able to maintain \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery momentum until 2022. \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery will strengthen to a level of 5.2 percent in 2022 if Indonesia manages to avoid more new waves of Covid-19 infection.\par \par \uc2 According to the \uc2 World \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank\b0 \highlight\b \highlight22\uc2 , Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will grow by 3.7 percent this year. Meanwhile, the government has targetted that Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth can reach 3.5 to 4 percent this year.\par \par \uc2 "The Covid-19 pandemic remains a challenge for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . However, Indonesia can still control the pandemic up until now. Although the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  had experienced a slow down because of the delta variant between July and August, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in Indonesia can still be managed well," Airlangga said.\par \par \uc2 Airlangga said that Indonesia has successfully suppressed the unemployment number to avoid experiencing a significant increase, specifically during the period of the Delta variant infection. Although the loss of income for workers continue to occur, the expansion of social assistance programs organized by the government has managed to mitigate the risk of increasing poverty rate.\par \par \uc2 In terms of vaccination, Indonesia had vaccinated over 70 percent of its residents with the first dose and more than 50 percent for the second dose. The government had also beginning to commence vaccination program for children.\par \par \uc2 Several monetary and financial policies continue to remain accomodative by taking into consideration many potential for risks and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , including possibilites of new Covid-19 variant infections, which makes the acceleration of vaccination program is important as well as incresing capacities for testing, tracing, and treatment.\par \par \uc2 "The government had also implemented various structural reform regulations, such as the Work Creation Law and the \b \highlight22\uc2 Tax Regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  Harmonization Law to continue to push for sustainable and inclusive development," Airlangga said.\par \par \uc2 ANTARA\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://statik.tempo.co/data/2021/11/25/id_1069148/1069148_720.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par \uc2 Document TEMPOE0020211218ehci0008e\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
