\par\par \b \uc2 Govt expects GDP growth above 5% in Q4\b0\par\par\uc2 Vincent Fabian Thomas, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \uc2 503 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 December 2021\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 5\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2021 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 The government expects GDP growth in the final quarter of this year to exceed 5 percent, thanks to eased mobility restrictions and a recovering global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Finance Minister \uc2 Sri Mulyani Indrawati\uc2  said on Tuesday that the domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery had strengthened following the interruption by the Delta COVID-19 variant in July and August.\par \par \uc2 Growth in consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , exports, production and more had accelerated though the fourth quarter, she said.\par \par \uc2 "For 2021, we estimate our GDP growth to reach 3.5 to 4 percent, with annual GDP growth in the fourth quarter projected to be above 5 percent. The acceleration seems to remain strong," Sri Mulyani said during the monthly state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  press conference.\par \par \uc2 The country's COVID-19 response helped bring down the virus caseload, which in turn allowed for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity to resume.\par \par \uc2 Sri Mulyani asked the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  and businesses to continue to behave responsibly so as not to spoil the improved COVID-19 situation, especially amid the increasing threat posed by the Omicron variant.\par \par \uc2 The summer spike in the COVID-19 caseload, by prompting wide-scale restrictions to travel, business and leisure activity, took a serious toll on the domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Indonesia's GDP growth slowed to 3.51 percent year-on-year (yoy) in the third quarter from more than 7 percent in the second.\par \par \uc2 "Do not let Omicron disrupt the projection and this momentum. We will keep saying this, so that everyone [helps preserve] this recovery," Sri Mulyani said.\par \par \uc2 The ministry revealed that state revenue grew by 19.4 percent yoy to Rp 1.7 quadrillion (US$117.9 billion) in November, mainly due to growing \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity lifting revenue of companies engaged in manufacturing and trade.\par \par \uc2 Higher prices for commodities like coal, palm oil and minerals as well as oil and gas also played a role in increasing state revenue, particularly though nontax revenue and export \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "We project that, until the end of this year, God willing, all state revenue components will exceed the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  targets," Sri Mulyani said, adding that the government had reached 97.5 percent of its revenue target in November.\par \par \uc2 Sri Mulyani went on to say that the government would remain vigilant amid global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  like the \uc2 United States Federal Reserve\uc2 's monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and other factors that cast a shadow over the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery trajectory.\par \par \uc2 The government would continue to assess the situation and ensure its readiness to deploy \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  measures if needed, she said, mentioning specifically \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  cuts incentivizing the purchase of new vehicles and properties.\par \par \uc2 "If [the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ] still needs our support, we will continue [providing \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2 ]; otherwise, we will make some adjustments," Sri Mulyani said.\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms would also be the government's focus next year, particularly derivative regulations following the Harmonized \b \highlight22\uc2 Tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  Law.\par \par \uc2 The ministry said the planned use of personal identity numbers as taxpayer numbers was expected to be realized in 2023 amid the implementation of a new \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  system.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020211222ehcn0000d\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
